It would also entail more risk than a COH bot perma camped some random place would, and would cost a hell of a lot more $ ooo economic problem solver inc.<br>
<br>
Thats about as unpowerful as an ability can be really I dont see what the fuss is about, one class shouldnt have the cornerstone on one ability anyway, or at least thats what bards keep saying when they cant do something like pick locks....<br>
<br>
Really, these arguments so far arent reasons at all why it shouldnt be doable.<br>
